### Support buffer reuse for intrinsics
StorageRewrite can reuse/inplace buffers for load/store, and other halide based operations, but doesn't support for intrinsics, just treat intrinsics opaque, since for different backends, thet may get different behaviors/requirements.  
For ASICs, we may have lots of intrinsics when we are in storage rewrite pass, if we can reuse buffers for these intrinsics, we can get more performance. For example, we can have better performance, if we do inplace as below.

```
vadd(tvm_access_ptr(0.000000h, Res_UB_F16, 7936, 7936, 2), tvm_access_ptr(0.000000h, Res_UB_F16, 7936, 7936, 1), tvm_access_ptr(0.000000h, Res_UB_F16, 16, 128, 1))
copy_matrix_cc_to_ubuf(tvm_access_ptr(0.000000h, Res_UB_F16, 0, 63488, 2), tvm_access_ptr(0.000000h, Res_UB_F16, 0, 63488, 1))
```


### How to support this
The main idea is registering hooks for different backends.

The steps to do this

- Expose target name for StorageRewrite
  One way is adding a target name for StorageRewrite. to do this, also we need to a target name in lower api 
  `Stmt StorageRewrite(Stmt stmt, const std::string& target)`

  Another way is having a function like tvm::Target Target::current_target, but this api only works for "with target", we can't get the current target in all passes in build function.

- When check the inplace of stmt, add a hook for Evaluate(intrinsics is always inside of Evaluate node)
```
@@ -229,7 +232,11 @@ class InplaceOpVerifier : public IRVisitor {
     } else if (stmt->is_type<Store>()) {
       Visit_(static_cast<const Store*>(stmt));
+     }else if (stmt->is_type<Evaluate>()){
+      if (target_.empty()) return false;
+      std::string reuse_hook = "tvm."+target_+".intrin_inplace";
+      const PackedFunc* f = runtime::Registry::Get(reuse_hook);
+      if (f == nullptr) return false;
+      result_ = f(static_cast<const Evaluate*>(stmt));
     } else {
       return false;
     }
```

- Define a target packed function, in which we do analysis for Evaluate node, return the result of inplace for the intrinsics, and register this function to tvm.target.intrin_inplace, both python or c++ packed function is ok.

